  "data_availability": "Application to biobank access committee required",
  "notes": "The largest deeply phenotyped ME/CFS biobank with matched healthy and multiple sclerosis disease controls. Participants were clinically assessed and met both Fukuda (CDC 1994) and Canadian Consensus (CCC 2003) criteria for ME/CFS. Specimens include serum, PBMC, RNA, and whole blood — valuable for biomarker discovery. Not a prospective inception cohort; cross-sectional with retrospective illness duration data. Illness duration ranges widely (new-onset to decades). Placed under unknown-trigger as the cohort includes participants with both post-infectious and gradual onset; the database records ME/CFS as the outcome, not the trigger.",
